be.unamur.info.b314.compiler.main

Class WhenScope

  • java.lang.Object
    • be.unamur.info.b314.compiler.main.WhenScope
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Scope

    public class WhenScope
extends java.lang.Object
implements Scope
    The WhenScope is an implementation of the Scope interface. This class can be used to represent a When Scope. A Global Scope has Symbols, Children, an Enclosing Scope and a Name.
    Author:
    Valentin Eggermont - valentin.eggermont@student.unamur.be, Christelle Trinon - christelle.trinon@student.unamur.be
